Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Remove the @puff pastry sheet{½} from your fridge. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}. Trim the @carrot{1} (no need to peel), then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into 1cm pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. While the pan gets hot, chop the @paneer{226} into 2cm chunks.

Once hot, add the paneer to the pan and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Fry until golden all over, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn every ~{1-2%minutes}. Once golden, transfer to a #bowl{} and pop your pan back on medium-high heat. Add a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry, then add the onion and carrot and fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Season the veg with salt and pepper, then add the garlic, @tomato puree{30} and @pasanda style seasoning{2} (add less seasoning if you don't like it too hot) along with the fried paneer. Stir and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @coconut milk{200}, @water{100} for the dal, @vegetable stock paste{10} and lentils. Bring to the boil and simmer until the mixture has thickened, ~{6-8%minutes}. Stir occasionally and add a splash more water if you need to.

Once the lentil mixture is cooked, taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it, then transfer it to an appropriately sized ovenproof #pie dish{}. Cover with the puff pastry, trimming off any excess. Press some of the pastry over the side of the dish if you can, or just sit it on top. Make a small hole in the middle - this allows the steam to escape.

> TIP: Brush the pastry with a little milk if you have some.

Bake your pie on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown, ~{15-20%minutes}.

In the meantime, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}.

Once baked, allow the pie to stand for ~{2%minutes}. Serve in #bowls{} with the spring onion sprinkled on top. Enjoy!

> STEP 5 MOD: If you've chosen to add broccoli florets to your meal, once you've prepped your spring onion, bring a #medium saucepan{} of water to the boil with 0.5 tsp of salt. Once the pie is 5 mins from being cooked, add the @broccoli florets{200} to the boiling water and cook until just tender, ~{3-5%minutes}. Then drain in a #colander{}. Serve alongside the pie.